<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1436,222,607]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,475,499]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Nobili, G." box="[323,490,474,498]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="158 - 164" refId="ref51316" refString="Nobili, G. (1905 a) Decapodes nouveaux des cotes d'Arabie et du Golfe Persique (Diagnoses preliminaires). Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, Paris, 11, 158 - 164." type="journal article" year="1905">Nobili (1905a)</bibRefCitation>
described this species from the Persian Gulf on the coast of the 
<collectingCountry box="[1226,1287,474,498]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">UAE</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Apel, M." box="[1299,1436,474,498]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" refId="ref45060" refString="Apel, M. (2001) Taxonomie und Zoogeographie der Brachyura, Paguridea und Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Decapoda) des Persisch-Arabischen Golfes. Unpublished doctoral thesis, Johann Wolfgang Goethe-Universitat, Frankfurt a. M., 268 pp." type="book" year="2001">Apel (2001)</bibRefCitation>
recorded this species from the Gulf of 
<collectingCountry box="[599,667,510,534]" name="Oman" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Oman</collectingCountry>
for the first time. The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Alcock, 1895" authorityName="Alcock" authorityYear="1895" box="[1011,1320,510,534]" class="Malacostraca" family="Epialtidae" genus="Menaethiops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1011,1156,510,534]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Menaethiops</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Alcock, A." box="[1165,1320,510,534]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="157 - 291" refId="ref44142" refString="Alcock, A. (1895) Material for a carcinological Fauna of India. No. 1. The Brachyura Oxyrhyncha. Journal of the Asiatic Society of Bengal, 64 (2), 157 - 291." type="journal article" year="1895">Alcock, 1895</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, currently contains 15 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Ng, P. K. L. &amp; Guinot, D. &amp; Davie, P. J. F." box="[388,560,546,571]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="1 - 286" refId="ref51230" refString="Ng, P. K. L., Guinot, D. &amp; Davie, P. J. F. (2008) Systema Brachyurorum: Part I. An annotated checklist of extant brachyuran crabs of the world. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, Supplement 17, 1 - 286." type="journal article" year="2008">
Ng 
<emphasis box="[432,483,547,571]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">et al</emphasis>
. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
), but a sound taxonomic study is needed, since more new species wait to be discovered within that genus.
</paragraph>
